Definition.WordDefinition:
Swish \Swish\, v. t. [From the sound. Cf. {Swash}.] 1. To flourish, so as to make the sound swish. --Coleridge. [1913 Webster]
2. To flog; to lash. [Slang] --Thackeray. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Swish \Swish\, v. i. To dash; to swash. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Swish \Swish\, n. 1. A sound of quick movement, as of something whirled through the air. [Colloq.] [1913 Webster]
2. (Naut.) Light driven spray. [Eng.] [1913 Webster]
